Currently a process object OnExit event only fired with no parameter besides the self object. But we don't know whether the process exited normally or not.

So I hope that the OnExit event can attach a parameter which indicated the process exit type(normally exit or abnormally exit).

```c#
var a = new Process();
a.OnExit = (obj, state) => {
    switch (state)
    {
    case ProcessExitType.Normally:
        ....
        break;
    case ProcessExitType.Abnormally
        ....
        break;
    }
.....
```

Following example produces incorrect output:
```cs
using System;
using System.Threading;
using System.Threading.Tasks;

namespace Hello
{
    internal class Program
    {
        [ThreadStatic]
        static int value;

        static void M()
        {
            value++;
            Console.WriteLine("T1: " + value);
        }

        private static void Main(string[] args)
        {
            value = 25;

            var t = new Thread(new ThreadStart(Program.M));
            t.Start();
            t.Join();

            Console.WriteLine("Main Thread : " + value);
        }
    }
}
```
```
$ ./Hello
T1: 26
Aborted (core dumped)
```
Expected output:
```
T1: 1
Main Thread : 25
```
Abort occurs due to multithreading https://github.com/dotnet/corert/issues/6405

